This makes a kernel-headers package

You may only need this for wine or software targeting kernel user space calls.
Out-of-tree kernel modules (NVIDIA, VirtualBox, ZFS, custom drivers)

The kernel headers you use to build software should match the running kernel exactly.
Pleas dont rebuild all slackware15 base software.

You should not install this on top of slackware kernel-headers

upgradepkg --reinstall /tmp/kernel-headers

blacklist kernel-headers from slackpkg

If the source is /usr/src/linux-6.4.7-zen
You may need to set VERSION to 6.4.7-zen
